A serene garden with a majestic Quan Yin Buddha
Mar 2020 ‚Ä¢ Couples
A short 10 minute drive from the hotel strip brings you to this serene garden with a majestic Quan Yon Buddha that takes your breath away as you gaze up to her delightful face. The vast number of sculptures and mature bonsais keep you entertained. You may peek into a few temples as you stroll the grounds. For those of you looking for monkeys, hang around the parking lot for a bit of mischievous fun... All in all, an hour well spent.
Written March 11, 2020
otasaraus
Canberra, Australia21 contributions
Beautiful architecture, delightful monkeys
Lady Buddha herself is an incredible sight. The bonsai gardens surrounding were elegant and understated.

The section in front of the lady Buddha is surrounded by the red face monkeys, they are an absolute treat to watch. Finding snacks wherever they can and just going about their business. A definite trip highlight.
Written January 27, 2020
Ann K
Reykjavik, Iceland31 contributions
Interesting visit of Buddhist temple
If you take a scooter the place is about a 20-30 minutes drive from downtown Da Nang, outside the city. You can park your scooter and walk around, visiting the Lady Buddha statue and the temple area. It's a nice visit popular also with local tourists, giving some insights into local culture and religion.
